1
00:00:35,009 --> 00:00:36,172
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,172 --> 00:00:37,115
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,115 --> 00:00:38,207
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:44,901 --> 00:00:48,652
[Episode 4]
<i>♪ Why am I standing on this road? ♪</i>

5
00:00:48,652 --> 00:00:52,592
<i>♪ Is this really my path? ♪</i>

6
00:00:52,592 --> 00:00:54,796
<i>♪ At the end of this road ♪</i>

7
00:00:54,796 --> 00:00:59,677
<i>♪ Will my dream come true? ♪</i>

8
00:00:59,677 --> 00:01:04,188
<i>♪ I want to say with confidence
that this is my path ♪</i>

9
00:01:04,188 --> 00:01:06,503
- Hey, hey.
<i>- ♪ Never regret it... ♪</i>

10
00:01:12,556 --> 00:01:16,473
You think you're walking straight?

11
00:01:16,473 --> 00:01:18,798
What's that supposed to mean?

12
00:01:18,798 --> 00:01:20,904
Because I got fired?

13
00:01:20,904 --> 00:01:22,767
No, that's not it.

14
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:26,207
Where are you going? What road is this?

15
00:01:26,207 --> 00:01:28,525
Same road as you.

16
00:01:28,525 --> 00:01:29,861
What?

17
00:01:29,861 --> 00:01:32,587
I'm making movies with you.

18
00:01:44,141 --> 00:01:48,349
<i>- ♪ What am I dreaming of... ♪</i>
- Hey, hey! Wait!

19
00:01:48,349 --> 00:01:51,881
<i>♪ Who is that dream really for? ♪</i>

20
00:01:51,881 --> 00:01:56,277
<i>♪ If I make it come true,
will I finally smile... ♪</i>

21
00:02:21,738 --> 00:02:22,786
Gosh.

22
00:02:23,432 --> 00:02:24,624
What the...

23
00:02:24,624 --> 00:02:27,040
You're insane, Ju Yi Jae!

24
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:46,723
Ian.

25
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:54,978
What?

26
00:02:55,626 --> 00:02:57,224
- Someone's here.
- Ian?

27
00:02:57,224 --> 00:02:59,400
Let's go get some breakfast.

28
00:03:00,087 --> 00:03:01,939
In Uk.

29
00:03:07,651 --> 00:03:09,206
It's freezing.

30
00:03:10,247 --> 00:03:11,640
Huh?

31
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:17,637
Are you in there?

32
00:03:17,637 --> 00:03:19,957
What are you doing?

33
00:03:19,957 --> 00:03:21,762
Yeah, I'm in the shower.

34
00:03:21,762 --> 00:03:23,180
Okay.

35
00:03:29,575 --> 00:03:31,719
Sounds like a rough shower.

36
00:03:31,719 --> 00:03:34,619
It'd be a problem if you died in there alone.

37
00:03:34,619 --> 00:03:37,685
For me, for the hotel...

38
00:03:37,685 --> 00:03:41,695
You too, probably. Going out like that.

39
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:44,512
Or maybe...

40
00:03:44,512 --> 00:03:46,455
You'd be proud.

41
00:03:46,455 --> 00:03:48,118
You're hot.

42
00:03:48,118 --> 00:03:50,230
Come to the lounge.

43
00:04:22,055 --> 00:04:23,995
What were you thinking?

44
00:04:25,195 --> 00:04:27,353
I didn't know where to look.

45
00:04:27,353 --> 00:04:28,814
Your eyes?

46
00:04:30,493 --> 00:04:32,287
They're puffy.

47
00:04:51,259 --> 00:04:52,844
Hey!

48
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:56,296
You should've told me you had a roommate.

49
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,874
I did.

50
00:04:57,874 --> 00:05:01,076
He's next door, not my roommate.

51
00:05:01,076 --> 00:05:02,701
Wait outside.

52
00:05:02,701 --> 00:05:05,341
We need to talk about last night.

53
00:05:07,149 --> 00:05:08,922
Don't go.

54
00:05:37,326 --> 00:05:41,483
Normally, this is where the girl runs.

55
00:05:41,483 --> 00:05:42,777
But I'm different.

56
00:05:42,777 --> 00:05:44,973
Sounds rehearsed.

57
00:05:46,907 --> 00:05:48,990
How did I get here?

58
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:51,870
I remember saying I'd make movies with you.

59
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:54,239
Fill me in after that.

60
00:05:55,186 --> 00:05:58,713
So that's where you blacked out?

61
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:04,677
I didn't know you were that bold.

62
00:06:04,677 --> 00:06:05,821
"Bold?"

63
00:06:05,821 --> 00:06:07,297
Me?

64
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:11,720
What exactly did I do?

65
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,249
Ju Yi Jae.

66
00:06:14,903 --> 00:06:16,591
You listed your place.

67
00:06:16,591 --> 00:06:18,191
What?

68
00:06:20,483 --> 00:06:23,208
It's a bit old, but the layout is great.

69
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:25,993
It faces south, so it gets great light.

70
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,168
You're the tenant, right?

71
00:06:28,168 --> 00:06:30,414
- Hello.
- The landlord called me.

72
00:06:30,414 --> 00:06:33,052
You even gave us the door code.

73
00:06:33,052 --> 00:06:35,612
Thank you so much.

74
00:06:35,612 --> 00:06:36,998
I did?

75
00:06:36,998 --> 00:06:42,028
I've been running around all morning
just to show this place.

76
00:06:42,028 --> 00:06:46,012
<i>I really am... my own regret.</i>

77
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:50,697
- I really like this place.
- Right?

78
00:06:50,697 --> 00:06:52,654
Look over here too.

79
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:56,245
- Hello.
- Hi.

80
00:06:56,245 --> 00:06:57,935
- Hello.
- Hello.

81
00:06:57,935 --> 00:07:00,516
- Hello.
- Hello.

82
00:07:00,516 --> 00:07:02,022
Hello.

83
00:07:02,022 --> 00:07:03,798
Hello.

84
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:17,874
[Film Screenplay and Directing Agreement]

85
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:24,497
- Yi Jae.
- Yeah?

86
00:07:24,497 --> 00:07:27,680
Is that seal heavy?

87
00:07:29,885 --> 00:07:31,248
A little.

88
00:07:31,248 --> 00:07:33,750
Mine felt heavy too on my first contract.

89
00:07:34,810 --> 00:07:39,699
Maybe try thinking of it another way.

90
00:07:41,702 --> 00:07:47,661
This isn't a world
where no one notices if you disappear.

91
00:07:47,661 --> 00:07:50,811
This story is yours.

92
00:07:50,811 --> 00:07:54,857
You started it, so you get to finish it.

93
00:07:54,857 --> 00:07:58,526
That means you write it and direct it.

94
00:07:59,484 --> 00:08:04,369
And I'll be with you the whole way.

95
00:08:04,369 --> 00:08:06,181
To the end.

96
00:08:14,689 --> 00:08:16,011
[Sealed by Ju Yi Jae]

97
00:08:17,662 --> 00:08:19,163
Finally.

98
00:08:20,071 --> 00:08:22,553
Now it really begins.

99
00:08:22,553 --> 00:08:24,097
Hello, I'm Seo In Uk.

100
00:08:24,097 --> 00:08:25,677
Hello.

101
00:08:25,677 --> 00:08:31,163
I'll do everything I can
so you can focus on the script.

102
00:08:31,163 --> 00:08:32,299
Thank you.

103
00:08:32,299 --> 00:08:34,001
What about the studio?

104
00:08:34,853 --> 00:08:38,306
She doesn't have a place right now.

105
00:08:38,306 --> 00:08:39,976
Why would you say that?

106
00:08:39,976 --> 00:08:42,330
So that's why you were at the hotel.

107
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:45,321
- Sorry?
- I saw a pair of unfamiliar shoes.

108
00:08:45,321 --> 00:08:48,189
We just met but...

109
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:57,277
I've seen your shoes.

110
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:04,907
- I'm sorry.
- No need.

111
00:09:04,907 --> 00:09:09,094
We're looking for a quiet house nearby.

112
00:09:09,094 --> 00:09:11,137
He insisted on that area.

113
00:09:11,137 --> 00:09:15,050
Please stay at the hotel
just until the studio is set up.

114
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:17,138
I can stay with a friend.

115
00:09:17,138 --> 00:09:19,334
I'm afraid I can't allow that.

116
00:09:19,334 --> 00:09:20,871
You need to write.

117
00:09:20,871 --> 00:09:22,983
The hotel will be better.

118
00:09:22,983 --> 00:09:26,416
- Yes, sir.
- I look forward to working with you.

119
00:09:28,099 --> 00:09:30,522
Same here.

120
00:09:37,056 --> 00:09:40,942
Ta-da! Here Comes Dong Hyun!

121
00:09:40,942 --> 00:09:42,901
He's better.

122
00:09:43,575 --> 00:09:45,219
Welcome.

123
00:09:45,219 --> 00:09:47,025
You've got a good eye.

124
00:09:47,025 --> 00:09:48,627
Perfect.

125
00:09:50,541 --> 00:09:53,458
- Producer Kyung?
- Yes?

126
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:55,307
I'm Seo In Uk.

127
00:09:57,128 --> 00:09:59,437
It says Jaden.

128
00:09:59,437 --> 00:10:01,105
I'm Jaden too.

129
00:10:01,105 --> 00:10:03,307
I see.

130
00:10:03,307 --> 00:10:06,045
What does a film company want with me?

131
00:10:06,045 --> 00:10:09,760
Ju Yi Jae is still owed payment.

132
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,673
Ju Yi Jae?

133
00:10:11,673 --> 00:10:13,200
What?

134
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,556
How do you know her?

135
00:10:14,556 --> 00:10:17,163
She signed with us.

136
00:10:17,163 --> 00:10:19,493
In a way, I guess we owe you.

137
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:23,878
We'd been dying to sign her.

138
00:10:23,878 --> 00:10:26,606
- But loose ends still need tying up.
- Wait...

139
00:10:26,606 --> 00:10:28,716
What did she sign?

140
00:10:28,716 --> 00:10:29,980
And tie up what?

141
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:34,673
There must've been some mix-up.
I'll look into it first...

142
00:10:34,673 --> 00:10:36,230
No, no.

143
00:10:36,230 --> 00:10:38,058
You'd handle that yourself?

144
00:10:38,058 --> 00:10:40,970
Even your own work was too much trouble.

145
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:43,107
What are you talking about?

146
00:10:43,107 --> 00:10:45,770
Is that what Yi Jae said?

147
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:49,903
She's spreading lies because she's bitter.

148
00:10:49,903 --> 00:10:52,740
I'm not like that. You've got me wrong.

149
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:55,941
No standard contract.
Driving for you. Editing for you.

150
00:10:55,941 --> 00:10:57,698
Clock-ins. Meetings.

151
00:10:57,698 --> 00:11:02,867
You gave unfair work to a contract worker,
then wrongfully fired her.

152
00:11:04,918 --> 00:11:07,676
Our legal team is good.

153
00:11:07,676 --> 00:11:10,642
They made it simple...

154
00:11:11,985 --> 00:11:14,182
so you won't be bothered.

155
00:11:14,182 --> 00:11:15,927
Take a look.

156
00:11:16,964 --> 00:11:18,782
What's that paper?

157
00:11:21,922 --> 00:11:23,241
Yeah?

158
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:45,980
Think of this as a warm-up
until the studio is ready.

159
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,746
- Don't push yourself.
- No.

160
00:11:47,746 --> 00:11:53,720
This amazing work setup
is bringing my creative soul back to life.

161
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:00,535
[One Hour Later]

162
00:12:01,628 --> 00:12:04,586
It has been dead for a while.

163
00:12:07,107 --> 00:12:08,543
Even old sparks can come back.

164
00:12:08,543 --> 00:12:11,556
Why don't you start by watching some movies?

165
00:12:11,556 --> 00:12:14,482
References. Very important.

166
00:12:20,058 --> 00:12:21,540
[Lead Actor, Go Sang Yeon]

167
00:12:23,985 --> 00:12:26,509
Is he ever on time?

168
00:12:26,509 --> 00:12:28,403
There he is.

169
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:31,479
He's not ready yet. Could you wait?

170
00:12:31,479 --> 00:12:33,199
He's already late.

171
00:12:33,199 --> 00:12:35,363
- Now you want more time?
- Sorry.

172
00:12:35,363 --> 00:12:37,658
It's my fault.

173
00:12:37,658 --> 00:12:39,995
You always cut Oh Ha Na slack.

174
00:12:39,995 --> 00:12:41,889
Why so hard on me?

175
00:12:41,889 --> 00:12:44,893
Just get me ready during rehearsal.

176
00:12:44,893 --> 00:12:48,113
Use someone close enough.

177
00:12:48,113 --> 00:12:49,197
Hey!

178
00:12:49,197 --> 00:12:51,530
Hey! You. White shirt.

179
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:54,034
- Come here.
- Go on.

180
00:12:56,486 --> 00:12:58,116
- Me?
- Yeah.

181
00:12:58,116 --> 00:13:00,609
Here. Scene 26.

182
00:13:00,609 --> 00:13:02,538
Rehearse for me.

183
00:13:02,538 --> 00:13:05,324
Good luck, Oh Ha Na.

184
00:13:08,737 --> 00:13:09,867
Cut!

185
00:13:09,867 --> 00:13:11,921
Okay!

186
00:13:11,921 --> 00:13:13,752
You're really good.

187
00:13:13,752 --> 00:13:17,166
It was just rehearsal, but I want to use that.

188
00:13:17,166 --> 00:13:18,936
How long have you acted?

189
00:13:18,936 --> 00:13:21,456
- I'd love to see you in my next project.
- Thank you.

190
00:13:21,456 --> 00:13:25,143
You've got the look and the emotion.

191
00:13:25,143 --> 00:13:26,653
Hey!

192
00:13:26,653 --> 00:13:28,553
Follow me.

193
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:35,742
There he goes again.

194
00:13:35,742 --> 00:13:37,481
Beats me.

195
00:13:37,481 --> 00:13:39,585
He's been on edge lately.

196
00:13:39,585 --> 00:13:41,491
It's not his first time.

197
00:13:41,491 --> 00:13:43,725
Why take it out on him?

198
00:13:49,431 --> 00:13:51,753
What's with you?

199
00:13:51,753 --> 00:13:54,331
- You laughed at me earlier.
- I didn't.

200
00:13:54,331 --> 00:13:59,338
They call me box-office poison,
so I'm a joke to you too?

201
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:03,055
- I didn't.
- I can see it in your eyes.

202
00:14:03,055 --> 00:14:04,715
Saw your chance?

203
00:14:04,715 --> 00:14:06,265
Eyeing my spot?

204
00:14:06,265 --> 00:14:08,144
I didn't.

205
00:14:08,144 --> 00:14:11,064
- You told me to, senior.
- "Senior?"

206
00:14:11,064 --> 00:14:13,192
Since when am I your senior?

207
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,860
That's enough, Mr. Go.

208
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:18,951
"Mr. Go?"

209
00:14:18,951 --> 00:14:20,548
You've got guts.

210
00:14:20,548 --> 00:14:22,554
Show some respect.

211
00:14:25,368 --> 00:14:27,861
I'll leave if you're done.

212
00:14:27,861 --> 00:14:29,688
Look at this punk.

213
00:14:29,688 --> 00:14:32,212
You're nothing.

214
00:14:32,212 --> 00:14:34,698
So why are you standing so tall?

215
00:14:34,698 --> 00:14:36,569
Who's behind you?

216
00:14:36,569 --> 00:14:39,426
Got some rich lady backing you?

217
00:14:39,426 --> 00:14:41,701
Any problem?

218
00:14:48,215 --> 00:14:51,066
- Have you lost it?
- You have.

219
00:14:51,066 --> 00:14:52,576
What...

220
00:14:52,576 --> 00:14:54,153
You two a thing?

221
00:14:54,153 --> 00:14:56,030
Yeah, we're close.

222
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:58,674
- Who are you to touch my friend?
- "Friend?"

223
00:14:58,674 --> 00:15:01,175
You don't have friends.
You barely went to school.

224
00:15:01,175 --> 00:15:02,846
Why wouldn't I?

225
00:15:02,846 --> 00:15:05,881
- Didn't you watch "Ha Na's High School?"
- You only clocked in on shoot days.

226
00:15:05,881 --> 00:15:09,857
- It's called "going to school," idiot.
- With cameras?

227
00:15:09,857 --> 00:15:13,180
I heard some great stories
from your high school days.

228
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:15,204
Your friends must've hated you.

229
00:15:15,204 --> 00:15:17,374
- What?
- Oh, right.

230
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:21,782
Not your friends. Your bullying victims.

231
00:15:23,321 --> 00:15:24,931
I apologized for that!

232
00:15:24,931 --> 00:15:28,109
People don't change.

233
00:15:28,109 --> 00:15:31,186
You should've outgrown the bully act back then.

234
00:15:31,186 --> 00:15:34,114
I dropped out after middle school.

235
00:15:35,859 --> 00:15:38,595
Real classy, asshole.

236
00:15:39,309 --> 00:15:41,629
Come on, friend. Let's go.

237
00:15:42,709 --> 00:15:44,013
Where are you going?

238
00:15:44,013 --> 00:15:46,019
Get back here!

239
00:15:46,019 --> 00:15:48,257
That's hot!

240
00:15:48,257 --> 00:15:50,424
She didn't put it out!

241
00:15:50,424 --> 00:15:52,888
Where's my manager? Report her!

242
00:15:52,888 --> 00:15:54,404
Hot!

243
00:19:10,271 --> 00:19:13,037
<i>Why did I close my eyes?</i>

244
00:19:27,752 --> 00:19:29,082
What?

245
00:19:29,082 --> 00:19:31,631
You want me to keep going?

246
00:19:32,508 --> 00:19:35,052
No, I don't.

247
00:19:35,052 --> 00:19:36,577
But...

248
00:19:38,946 --> 00:19:40,403
Gosh.

249
00:19:44,199 --> 00:19:46,036
Good night.

250
00:19:46,036 --> 00:19:48,061
Yeah. Good night.

251
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:49,865
Yeah. Bye.

252
00:19:49,865 --> 00:19:51,264
Bye.

253
00:20:14,570 --> 00:20:15,874
Wait.

254
00:20:15,874 --> 00:20:18,145
Why is he sleeping here?

255
00:20:24,432 --> 00:20:26,165
[In Uk]
<i>Coming back?</i>

256
00:20:27,316 --> 00:20:29,647
<i>Not coming back.</i>

257
00:21:20,618 --> 00:21:23,278
- Morning.
- Good morning.

258
00:21:34,191 --> 00:21:36,748
Looks like you didn't sleep well.

259
00:21:36,748 --> 00:21:38,394
Yeah...

260
00:21:40,812 --> 00:21:42,479
Eat up.

261
00:21:48,934 --> 00:21:50,771
No coffee?

262
00:22:07,286 --> 00:22:09,012
Think.

263
00:22:19,631 --> 00:22:21,508
[Nan Young's gaze turns toward Moo Gyeom]

264
00:22:37,187 --> 00:22:40,924
[Nothing's coming to me... Nothing]

265
00:22:43,192 --> 00:22:45,571
[Woo Soo Bin]
<i>Did you eat?</i>

266
00:22:45,571 --> 00:22:48,165
[Want to have lunch later?]
[Don't push yourself too hard]

267
00:22:48,165 --> 00:22:51,620
[Are you eating properly?]
[You worked hard today. Sleep well]

268
00:23:02,471 --> 00:23:04,149
Come on...

269
00:23:04,149 --> 00:23:08,555
Retirement feels so empty.

270
00:23:08,555 --> 00:23:10,539
I'm still perfectly fine.

271
00:23:10,539 --> 00:23:12,242
Why kick me out?

272
00:23:12,242 --> 00:23:15,281
Tell me about it.

273
00:23:15,896 --> 00:23:20,033
Young guys move up,
and suddenly we're old news.

274
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:23,951
Those young punks...

275
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,919
Well, not always.

276
00:23:31,919 --> 00:23:34,899
Youth unemployment is terrible too.

277
00:23:34,899 --> 00:23:38,465
Plenty of them just goof off all day.

278
00:23:38,465 --> 00:23:42,010
Kids these days have it too easy.

279
00:23:42,010 --> 00:23:44,281
- Enough. Stop.
- Why?

280
00:23:52,978 --> 00:23:54,862
I'm not just goofing off.

281
00:23:54,862 --> 00:23:57,256
I'm struggling, sir.

282
00:24:07,057 --> 00:24:08,161
Yu Geon.

283
00:24:08,161 --> 00:24:10,288
That event you mentioned.

284
00:24:10,288 --> 00:24:12,231
Did they find someone?

285
00:24:14,532 --> 00:24:16,439
You said you were busy writing.

286
00:24:16,439 --> 00:24:17,832
Yu Geon.

287
00:24:17,832 --> 00:24:19,562
Will you be in my movie?

288
00:24:19,562 --> 00:24:23,162
Come on. You know I hate that.

289
00:24:23,162 --> 00:24:26,812
Please don't give me even a tiny role.

290
00:24:26,812 --> 00:24:27,842
[Staff Only]

291
00:24:27,842 --> 00:24:29,431
- Hello.
- Yeah...

292
00:24:29,431 --> 00:24:31,875
I figured.

293
00:24:31,875 --> 00:24:32,991
Don't worry.

294
00:24:32,991 --> 00:24:37,404
Tiny role or not, I can't even do my own job.

295
00:24:37,404 --> 00:24:42,550
I can't write a single word,
so I'm here to make some cash.

296
00:24:43,202 --> 00:24:45,699
What does Soo Bin say?

297
00:24:45,699 --> 00:24:48,039
I'm dodging him.

298
00:24:48,039 --> 00:24:49,769
What am I going to do?

299
00:24:49,769 --> 00:24:53,344
I tell myself it's fine, but I can't calm down.

300
00:24:53,344 --> 00:24:56,488
That blinking cursor makes my heart race.

301
00:24:56,488 --> 00:24:58,018
And most of all...

302
00:24:58,018 --> 00:25:01,352
I'm scared Soo Bin will be disappointed.

303
00:25:02,049 --> 00:25:04,255
You must want to impress him.

304
00:25:06,378 --> 00:25:07,958
Good luck.

305
00:25:20,776 --> 00:25:22,478
Ju Yi Jae.

306
00:25:30,886 --> 00:25:32,706
Ju Yi Jae!

307
00:25:59,314 --> 00:26:01,356
Get in.

308
00:26:17,039 --> 00:26:18,179
Do you read the comments?

309
00:26:18,179 --> 00:26:19,680
[Something's off]
[They freeze when they lock eyes]

310
00:26:20,334 --> 00:26:22,143
You think viewers are stupid?

311
00:26:22,143 --> 00:26:25,073
Everyone can tell you two hate each other!

312
00:26:25,073 --> 00:26:26,573
You kicked his shin?

313
00:26:26,573 --> 00:26:27,731
Burned him with a cigarette?

314
00:26:27,731 --> 00:26:30,416
Why should I hear that crap from Hyeon Gu?

315
00:26:30,416 --> 00:26:32,440
Who's Hyeon Gu?

316
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,397
Sang Yeon's CEO!

317
00:26:34,397 --> 00:26:37,355
Stop picking fights with him.

318
00:26:37,355 --> 00:26:39,817
Handling your costar is part of the job.

319
00:26:39,817 --> 00:26:43,257
Why do you clash with every rom-com lead?

320
00:26:43,257 --> 00:26:47,254
They start it. They try to put me in my place.

321
00:26:47,254 --> 00:26:50,741
- What?
- They all think they're kings.

322
00:26:50,741 --> 00:26:53,277
But you know what's worse?

323
00:26:53,277 --> 00:26:56,248
To everyone else,
I probably look just like them.

324
00:26:56,248 --> 00:26:59,172
So what? Just stay with your own kind.

325
00:26:59,172 --> 00:27:01,772
Don't come down and get your feet dirty.

326
00:27:01,772 --> 00:27:02,925
And...

327
00:27:02,925 --> 00:27:07,266
Isn't that a little hypocritical
on your way to a luxury event?

328
00:27:09,079 --> 00:27:10,323
- Director Kang!
- Yes.

329
00:27:10,323 --> 00:27:13,823
- Drop me at the next intersection!
- The next intersection?

330
00:27:13,823 --> 00:27:15,093
- Over there...
- Yeah.

331
00:27:15,093 --> 00:27:18,278
We're in the left lane, but I'll try.

332
00:27:27,611 --> 00:27:30,835
Hello. Please try this scent.

333
00:27:30,835 --> 00:27:32,056
Thank you.

334
00:27:32,056 --> 00:27:35,311
Hello. Please try this scent.

335
00:27:37,827 --> 00:27:39,503
Thank you.

336
00:27:40,329 --> 00:27:42,581
Hello. Try this...

337
00:27:45,076 --> 00:27:47,076
Why'd you skip me?

338
00:27:49,069 --> 00:27:52,232
- At least act happy to see me.
- I'm not.

339
00:27:52,232 --> 00:27:53,810
Ever heard of manners?

340
00:27:53,810 --> 00:27:55,893
Depends on you.

341
00:28:00,102 --> 00:28:02,301
There's someone I'm happy to see.

342
00:28:06,871 --> 00:28:09,069
What's with you two?

343
00:28:09,069 --> 00:28:10,909
Is he your manager?

344
00:28:12,125 --> 00:28:13,862
Are you... my manager?

345
00:28:13,862 --> 00:28:15,922
No. I meant you.

346
00:28:15,922 --> 00:28:18,839
- Me?
- You're pretty casual.

347
00:28:18,839 --> 00:28:20,874
So are you.

348
00:28:21,682 --> 00:28:25,852
Your Korean is perfect.
Why only speak English at the audition?

349
00:28:25,852 --> 00:28:29,623
Because it was in America. And this is Korea.

350
00:28:31,089 --> 00:28:32,857
Are you close with him?

351
00:28:32,857 --> 00:28:35,387
No. He's obviously older than me.

352
00:28:35,387 --> 00:28:38,912
We were just neighbors for a bit as kids.

353
00:28:38,912 --> 00:28:40,581
"Neighbors?"

354
00:28:40,581 --> 00:28:41,906
"For a bit?"

355
00:28:41,906 --> 00:28:44,286
Never be his friend.

356
00:28:57,590 --> 00:28:58,906
How do you know her?

357
00:28:58,906 --> 00:29:01,300
- Curious?
- Yes.

358
00:29:01,300 --> 00:29:02,779
I'm a director.

359
00:29:02,779 --> 00:29:03,975
She's an actress.

360
00:29:03,975 --> 00:29:06,204
That's it.

361
00:29:06,204 --> 00:29:08,824
At least we're not neighbors.

362
00:29:08,824 --> 00:29:10,786
That's not the way.

363
00:29:10,786 --> 00:29:12,545
You know where I'm going?

364
00:29:12,545 --> 00:29:14,846
Aren't you buying anything?

365
00:29:14,846 --> 00:29:17,503
- Will you give me a discount?
- Fine.

366
00:29:18,898 --> 00:29:21,202
- You like Rouvee, right?
- Yes!

367
00:29:21,202 --> 00:29:22,867
- You like it, right?
- Yes!

368
00:29:22,867 --> 00:29:25,482
Raise your hand if you do!

369
00:29:25,482 --> 00:29:28,142
If you love Rouvee, make some noise!

370
00:29:29,814 --> 00:29:33,191
Next up is the moment
you've all been waiting for.

371
00:29:33,191 --> 00:29:37,174
It's time for the lucky draw!

372
00:29:38,204 --> 00:29:41,735
This lucky draw will be picked
by our brand model,

373
00:29:41,735 --> 00:29:45,123
actress Oh Ha Na herself.

374
00:29:45,123 --> 00:29:49,557
Please welcome actress Oh Ha Na to the stage!

375
00:29:49,557 --> 00:29:51,820
Actress Oh Ha Na!

376
00:29:59,803 --> 00:30:03,271
I don't often get to meet fans this close.

377
00:30:03,271 --> 00:30:06,842
Let's have fun today.

378
00:30:08,146 --> 00:30:11,569
Who will be our lucky winner?

379
00:30:12,575 --> 00:30:14,606
- Number 38.
- Number 38!

380
00:30:14,606 --> 00:30:16,599
It's me! It's me!

381
00:30:21,084 --> 00:30:23,086
- Next is number 4.
- Number 4!

382
00:30:23,086 --> 00:30:24,219
Who is it?

383
00:30:24,219 --> 00:30:27,496
Number 4! Congrats!

384
00:30:28,348 --> 00:30:30,985
Please pick the last number.

385
00:30:30,985 --> 00:30:33,422
Last one! Last one!

386
00:30:33,422 --> 00:30:34,626
- Last one!
- Last one!

387
00:30:34,626 --> 00:30:37,018
Raise your hand if you want it!

388
00:31:39,434 --> 00:31:41,453
Sorry!

389
00:31:43,335 --> 00:31:44,620
Who are you?

390
00:31:44,620 --> 00:31:47,829
- Do you know me?
- This one's for you.

391
00:31:47,829 --> 00:31:50,222
The other one, I got bullied into buying.

392
00:31:50,222 --> 00:31:51,479
I get why now.

393
00:31:51,479 --> 00:31:55,070
Do you know me or not?

394
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:56,960
I know who you are.

395
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:59,277
And I know why you're here.

396
00:32:05,955 --> 00:32:08,994
Aren't you even mad?

397
00:32:14,273 --> 00:32:17,779
You finally made up your mind,

398
00:32:18,704 --> 00:32:22,197
but it didn't go the way you wanted. Right?

399
00:32:22,197 --> 00:32:25,051
You must've been scared.

400
00:32:25,051 --> 00:32:27,392
But that's normal.

401
00:32:30,495 --> 00:32:34,838
I'm scared too, that I'm just being selfish.

402
00:32:34,838 --> 00:32:39,301
What if I'm only making things harder for you?

403
00:32:41,179 --> 00:32:45,138
But we're trying to do something great.

404
00:32:49,224 --> 00:32:50,797
Yi Jae.

405
00:32:51,630 --> 00:32:57,239
Greatness isn't about making something amazing.

406
00:32:59,818 --> 00:33:02,360
Going all the way together,

407
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:04,489
that's what makes it great.

408
00:33:10,204 --> 00:33:12,487
Studio tomorrow, right?

409
00:33:13,246 --> 00:33:18,083
Think hard about
whether you're with me to the end.

410
00:33:21,465 --> 00:33:23,098
I should go.

411
00:34:03,118 --> 00:34:07,299
<i>Greatness isn't about making something amazing.</i>

412
00:34:08,843 --> 00:34:11,483
<i>Going all the way together,</i>

413
00:34:11,483 --> 00:34:13,510
<i>that's what makes it great.</i>

414
00:35:12,491 --> 00:35:14,058
Okay.

415
00:35:26,173 --> 00:35:27,978
Woo Soo Bin?

416
00:35:29,384 --> 00:35:31,001
It's you, right?

417
00:35:32,569 --> 00:35:34,139
Thank God.

418
00:35:34,139 --> 00:35:36,613
I've been looking everywhere.

419
00:35:36,613 --> 00:35:38,179
You're late.

420
00:35:38,179 --> 00:35:39,770
Trunk!

421
00:35:39,770 --> 00:35:41,200
Yeah.

422
00:35:48,167 --> 00:35:49,948
I'll load it.

423
00:35:59,245 --> 00:36:01,843
Let's go. To do something great.

424
00:36:09,271 --> 00:36:11,389
This is so nice, huh?

425
00:36:11,389 --> 00:36:13,843
- Yeah.
- The ocean is wonderful.

426
00:36:13,843 --> 00:36:15,282
Right.

427
00:36:24,222 --> 00:36:26,637
- What should we eat?
- Anything's fine.

428
00:36:26,637 --> 00:36:29,109
I know a great bibimbap place.

429
00:36:29,109 --> 00:36:30,460
Bibimbap?

430
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:32,659
Not bibimbap.

431
00:36:32,659 --> 00:36:34,766
- Something else.
- What do you even like?

432
00:36:34,766 --> 00:36:36,351
- Remember this place?
- Where?

433
00:36:36,351 --> 00:36:38,409
- There.
- Oh, there.

434
00:36:38,409 --> 00:36:42,442
- You don't remember, huh?
- Of course I do.

435
00:36:46,795 --> 00:36:48,508
I'm excited.

436
00:37:30,547 --> 00:37:32,367
Come on.

437
00:37:33,782 --> 00:37:34,988
Mom.

438
00:37:34,988 --> 00:37:36,388
What?

439
00:37:36,388 --> 00:37:38,412
What do you want me to be?

440
00:37:38,412 --> 00:37:40,262
A decent human being.

441
00:37:40,262 --> 00:37:41,695
Agreed.

442
00:37:42,733 --> 00:37:44,418
Stop joking.

443
00:37:44,418 --> 00:37:46,415
Anything.

444
00:37:46,415 --> 00:37:49,796
I'm not asking what's for dinner.

445
00:37:49,796 --> 00:37:52,653
At least I can choose dinner.

446
00:37:52,653 --> 00:37:56,306
Kids never turn out the way you want.

447
00:37:56,306 --> 00:37:58,290
Treasure them? Adore them?

448
00:37:58,290 --> 00:38:01,021
What a joke.

449
00:38:01,951 --> 00:38:03,627
That's harsh to your fired daughter.

450
00:38:03,627 --> 00:38:06,571
You were always working yourself to death.

451
00:38:06,571 --> 00:38:07,827
It's for the best.

452
00:38:07,827 --> 00:38:09,852
Just find something else.

453
00:38:09,852 --> 00:38:14,708
You could work festivals nationwide
and still make a living.

454
00:38:14,708 --> 00:38:16,238
Just buy a car.

455
00:38:16,238 --> 00:38:18,412
Stop taking the bus.

456
00:38:19,471 --> 00:38:20,916
Mom.

457
00:38:21,765 --> 00:38:24,212
I came here to write.

458
00:38:25,183 --> 00:38:26,406
What?

459
00:38:26,406 --> 00:38:27,541
A movie.

460
00:38:27,541 --> 00:38:29,541
I want to try again.

461
00:38:32,898 --> 00:38:35,385
Here we go again.

462
00:38:35,385 --> 00:38:37,006
I told you so many times.

463
00:38:37,006 --> 00:38:41,664
That's for rich kids
with nothing to worry about.

464
00:38:42,494 --> 00:38:45,269
So Woo Soo Bin can, but I can't?

465
00:38:45,269 --> 00:38:46,996
Right.

466
00:38:46,996 --> 00:38:49,559
He went all the way to America and made it.

467
00:38:49,559 --> 00:38:52,212
His dad was against it, so he cut him off.

468
00:38:52,212 --> 00:38:56,815
That courage comes from
having something to fall back on.

469
00:38:57,830 --> 00:38:59,367
No wonder I live like this.

470
00:38:59,367 --> 00:39:02,329
Fine. I'll live my own life.

471
00:39:06,567 --> 00:39:08,451
Don't tell me this is because of him.

472
00:39:08,451 --> 00:39:10,181
I already signed.

473
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:11,737
I'm doing it with him.

474
00:39:11,737 --> 00:39:12,791
You little...

475
00:39:12,791 --> 00:39:15,091
Are you out of your mind?

476
00:39:15,091 --> 00:39:17,144
Anyone but him!

477
00:39:17,144 --> 00:39:19,012
Look what he did to you!

478
00:39:19,012 --> 00:39:20,088
Why?

479
00:39:20,088 --> 00:39:23,248
Because he's rich and I'm poor.
It's not his fault.

480
00:39:23,248 --> 00:39:26,778
If you're right, I should've left home.

481
00:39:26,778 --> 00:39:30,518
Family or not, I should've lived my life!

482
00:39:30,518 --> 00:39:33,433
What is that supposed to mean?

483
00:39:59,563 --> 00:40:01,620
Ju Yi Jae, come out.

484
00:40:01,620 --> 00:40:03,541
Hey.

485
00:40:04,368 --> 00:40:06,409
Eat breakfast!

486
00:40:22,050 --> 00:40:24,221
[Interbank Transfer: Security Deposit]

487
00:40:30,853 --> 00:40:34,062
Gosh! You scared me.

488
00:40:34,062 --> 00:40:35,980
- When did you get here?
- At dawn.

489
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:37,380
Why?

490
00:40:38,183 --> 00:40:40,086
I ran away.

491
00:40:40,722 --> 00:40:42,238
What?

492
00:40:47,546 --> 00:40:50,677
We're adapting the original draft.

493
00:40:50,677 --> 00:40:55,587
Updating a ten-year-old draft won't be easy.

494
00:40:55,587 --> 00:40:58,040
So let's start with the structure.

495
00:40:58,040 --> 00:41:02,203
So I broke it down by chapter and scene.

496
00:41:02,203 --> 00:41:03,694
When did you do all that?

497
00:41:03,694 --> 00:41:05,777
Whenever I could.

498
00:41:05,777 --> 00:41:07,123
You called that warming up?

499
00:41:07,123 --> 00:41:09,524
Even if we change lines or move scenes,

500
00:41:09,524 --> 00:41:11,860
the framework will hold.

501
00:41:13,066 --> 00:41:16,223
Are we really doing this every time?

502
00:41:16,223 --> 00:41:19,526
Sharing every word, comma, and period?

503
00:41:19,526 --> 00:41:20,949
Yes.

504
00:41:24,793 --> 00:41:26,223
<i>Seriously?</i>

505
00:41:26,223 --> 00:41:27,887
<i>I'm so embarrassed.</i>

506
00:41:27,887 --> 00:41:30,326
<i>It shows too much.</i>

507
00:41:30,326 --> 00:41:32,397
It's not a diary.

508
00:41:32,397 --> 00:41:35,411
This is efficient. We can sync in real time.

509
00:41:35,411 --> 00:41:38,421
I wanted to clean it up before showing you.

510
00:41:38,421 --> 00:41:40,213
Ju Yi Jae.

511
00:41:40,213 --> 00:41:42,588
We're co-writing this.

512
00:41:42,588 --> 00:41:44,805
We need to write as one.

513
00:41:44,805 --> 00:41:47,724
Until even we can't tell who wrote which scene.

514
00:41:47,724 --> 00:41:49,818
Okay, I'll catch up fast.

515
00:41:49,818 --> 00:41:51,615
Let's meet whenever we need to.

516
00:41:51,615 --> 00:41:53,262
And eat together.

517
00:41:53,262 --> 00:41:55,343
Share schedules too.

518
00:41:56,342 --> 00:41:58,005
Want to work out together?

519
00:41:58,005 --> 00:41:59,325
For efficiency.

520
00:41:59,325 --> 00:42:00,435
No, thank you.

521
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:03,133
Let's skip the workouts.

522
00:42:04,950 --> 00:42:07,318
- Let's start.
- Yeah.

523
00:42:07,916 --> 00:42:10,712
- I'll share the file first.
- Okay.

524
00:42:33,711 --> 00:42:34,848
<i>"Nan Young."</i>

525
00:42:34,848 --> 00:42:37,092
<i>"Graceful and proud."</i>

526
00:42:37,092 --> 00:42:40,201
<i>"Noble Young Master."</i>

527
00:42:40,201 --> 00:42:43,980
<i>"You are quite impatient."</i>

528
00:42:46,713 --> 00:42:48,003
<i>"Nan Young."</i>

529
00:42:48,003 --> 00:42:51,012
<i>"She tries to pull away."</i>

530
00:42:51,012 --> 00:42:56,955
<i>"Just then, Moo Gyeom pulls her by the waist."</i>

531
00:43:00,541 --> 00:43:02,274
<i>"Moo Gyeom."</i>

532
00:43:02,274 --> 00:43:05,640
<i>"Why shouldn't I be?"</i>

533
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:10,225
<i>"When your eyes are so full of love for me."</i>

534
00:43:14,010 --> 00:43:15,713
I like it.

535
00:43:23,646 --> 00:43:26,624
What? You only worked?

536
00:43:26,624 --> 00:43:27,988
How do you only work?

537
00:43:27,988 --> 00:43:29,607
Weren't you nervous?

538
00:43:29,607 --> 00:43:32,108
Nervous, my ass.

539
00:43:32,108 --> 00:43:33,452
Hey.

540
00:43:33,452 --> 00:43:34,876
I'm Ju Yi Jae.

541
00:43:34,876 --> 00:43:36,455
I'm not that easy.

542
00:43:36,455 --> 00:43:38,856
This isn't about being easy.

543
00:43:38,856 --> 00:43:41,125
A grown man and woman under one roof?

544
00:43:41,125 --> 00:43:43,328
What genre is that?

545
00:43:43,328 --> 00:43:46,538
Usually, romance.

546
00:43:46,538 --> 00:43:48,186
Wait.

547
00:43:49,329 --> 00:43:51,353
I need to be careful.

